These are basic Linux commands that every DevOps / Cloud engineer use :

1 . pwd : Print Working Directory
2 . ls : List files and directories.
3 . ls -l :    # detailed list
4 . ls -a  :   # show hidden files
5 . cd : Change Directory.
6 . cd .. : Go to parent directory (one level back).
7 . ls -ltr : List files sorted by time (latest last).
8 . touch : Create an empty file.
9 . vi : Open file in VI text editor.
10 . cat : Display file content.
11 . mkdir : Create directory.
12 . rm -r : Remove directory recursively.
13 . free -g : Check RAM memory usage in GB.
14 . nproc : Shows number of CPU cores.
15 . df -h : Shows disk space usage.
16 . top : Shows running processes + CPU + RAM usage in real time.
17 . man : It is used to read documentation of Linux commands directly in the terminal.
18 . sh or ./ : run shell scripts
19 . chmod : change file or directory permissions.
20 . history : list of commands you previously executed in the terminal.
21 . ps or ps -ef : view running processes.
